⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 70/120 – Find Gaps Between Transactions

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to calculate the number of days between consecutive transactions for each customer.


---

📊 Input Dataset

customer_id	transaction_date

101	2024-01-10
101	2024-01-20
101	2024-02-05
102	2024-03-01
102	2024-03-15



---

✅ Expected Output

customer_id	transaction_date	previous_transaction	gap_days

101	2024-01-10	NULL	NULL
101	2024-01-20	2024-01-10	10
101	2024-02-05	2024-01-20	16
102	2024-03-01	NULL	NULL
102	2024-03-15	2024-03-01	14



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.window import Window
from pyspark.sql.functions import lag, datediff, col

window_spec = (
    Window.partitionBy("customer_id")
          .orderBy("transaction_date")
)

result = (
    df.withColumn(
        "previous_transaction",
        lag("transaction_date").over(window_spec)
    )
    .withColumn(
        "gap_days",
        datediff(
            col("transaction_date"),
            col("previous_transaction")
        )
    )
)

result.show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Which functions are used?

Answer

lag()

datediff()



---

Q2. Common business use cases?

Answer

Customer inactivity

Subscription renewals

Fraud detection

Purchase frequency analysis



---

Q3. Can we detect customers inactive for more than 30 days?

Answer

Yes.

Filter:

.filter(col("gap_days") > 30)


