⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 71/120 – First Purchase & Last Purchase

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to display the first purchase date and last purchase date for every customer.


---

📊 Input Dataset

customer_id	purchase_date

101	2024-01-10
101	2024-03-20
101	2024-04-01
102	2024-02-15
102	2024-05-05



---

✅ Expected Output

customer_id	first_purchase	last_purchase

101	2024-01-10	2024-04-01
102	2024-02-15	2024-05-05



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import min, max

df.groupBy("customer_id").agg(
    min("purchase_date").alias("first_purchase"),
    max("purchase_date").alias("last_purchase")
).show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Why not use first() and last()?

Answer

Without a defined order, first() and last() don't necessarily return the earliest or latest date. min() and max() are the correct choice for date extremes.


---

Q2. Which functions are preferred?

Answer

min() → First purchase

max() → Last purchase



---

Q3. Business use cases?

Answer

Customer lifecycle analysis

Loyalty programs

Retention analysis

Customer tenure



